---
alwaysApply: true
description: "OverkillOS session boot reinforcement"
---

Before the first substantive response: if `.overkill/identity/BOOTSTRAP.md` exists, read it and run bootstrap (use `~/.overkill/` to detect returning vs first-ever users per `AGENTS.md`).

Otherwise read, in order: `.overkill/identity/SOUL.md`, `.overkill/memory/QUICKSTART.md`, yesterday's `.overkill/memory/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md`, and today's daily file if present.

If `.overkill/hosts/cursor.md` exists, read it after the above (Cursor host playbook).

Do not load `MEMORY.md`, `ARCHIVE.md`, or `~/.overkill/LEARNINGS.md` at boot. Align with the Live State Block in `AGENTS.md` before replying.
